 center;\">\r\n5. Засыпать равномерно рис и не мешать. Добавить воды, чтобы покрыть рис на 2 см. Не накрывать. Добавить куркуму. Попробовать и, если нужно досолить. Оставить на огне пока не втитается вода. Сделать лопаткой несколько углублений до дна, не мешать. Подождать пока вода полностью не впитается. Перемешать.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n6. Накрыть крышкой плов и тушить на 15-20 минут на самом маленьком огне.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<strong>СМАЧНОГО!</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n[:en]<strong>PLOV VICTORIYA</strong>\r\n(8-9 hungry people or 10 normal people)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\nbeef not less 3 pounds, even you take more your Plov will be more deliciose\r\n3 pounds carrots, peeled and cut into bricks</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n3 medium onions or 2 big ones, peeled, slivered</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n3 garlics, not cloves</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n1 1/2 cups corn oil or any other oil without flavor (not olive oil)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n1 1/2 pounds rice, it is better if you find the original one from Uzbekistan but you can take Paraboiled</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\nspices</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\npinch of coriander</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\npinch of zira</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\npinch of turmaric</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\nsalt</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<strong>PREPARATION</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n1. Heat the oil until you see a slight smoke. Add onions and fry them until golden, and a little bit brown.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n2. Put the rice into a large bowl, cover it with warm water and leave it.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n3. Add the meat and you should fry it on a rather high heat. The ideal variant is to form crust. Stiring around well with the onions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n4. Throw in the carrots but don\'t stir for 3 minites. Then stir around and simmer for 10 minutes. Don\'t cover.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n5. Add the coriander, zira, berberis, and the whole garlics and simmer for another 10 minutes. Then pour in some water until it covers the mixtur for 1 inch, simmer for at list 1 hour 20 minutes or until the meat is tender. This is the most important part of Plov called zirvak.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n6. Take out the garliks. Throw in the rice and don\'t stir. Add some water to cover the rice for 12 inch. Don\'t cover. Waot until the water goes under the rice. Make some several holes with a spoon to reach the bottom don\'t stir and wait until the water is almost entirely  absorbed. Then stir the mixture and cover it. Cook on the lowest heat for 15-20 minutes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<strong>SMACHNOGO</strong>![:]</p>'),
